Description: Lapis lazuli plaque decorated on one side in the form of two plumed cartouches; one containing a representation of a female deity, the other containing hieroglyphs giving the name and epithet of Nefertari, laterally pierced in three places, the other side inscribed with two columns of hieroglyphs giving the title and name lady of the house Iniuhay.
Curator's comments: Published Kitchen, Ram. Insc. Vol 2 p853
Bibliographic references: Hall 1913 / Catalogue of Egyptian scarabs, etc. in the British Museum (p.226)
Exhibition history: Exhibited: 1998/9 Oct-Jun, South Carolina, The Charleston Museum, Queens Commoners of the New Kingdom
Acquisition name: Purchased from: R J Moss & Co
